Value: JSON protocol parse error / JSON parse error
Comment: Failed to parse a Json request to engine, '}' on wrong place for instance. Do Not translate [JSON]. JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation

Value: Internal JSON protocol error / Internal JSON-RPC error
Comment: Internal error when setting up a request to engine. Do Not translate [JSON]. JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation

Value: Invalid JSON protocol parameters / Invalid method parameter(s)
Comment: Wrong parameters specified in a json request to engine. Do Not translate [JSON]. JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation

Value: Requested protocol method does not exist / Method does not exist
Comment: Requested protol method does not exist in engines API, could be wrong spelling

Value: Invalid JSON protocol request / Invalid JSON request
Comment: Something went wrong when handling a request. Do Not translate [JSON]. JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation

Value: Internal engine error
Comment: Something went wrong internally inside the engine. Likely low on resources (RAM).

Value: Internal engine error / Internal error
Comment: Something went wrong internally inside the engine. Likely a memory access violation.

Value: The request to the QBDI cluster failed
Comment: Generic message for any error on the BDI side, causing the request from the engine to BDI cluster to fail.

Value: Unknown error / Unknown error
Comment: Generic message for e.g. when the session has been killed or cannot be initialized due to unknown reasons.

Value: Unknown error / OK
Comment: Something unspecified happen

Value: Some data is not correctly specified. / Resource not set
Comment: For example, a Variable is not set as it should

Value: The resource could not be found. / Resource not found
Comment: Happens when a resource

Value: Resource already exists. / Resource already exists
Comment: Happens when a resource like a file or folder given was already existing

Value: Invalid path / Invalid path
Comment: Invalid document path. Invalid characters in document name e.g., \, //, .., <, >, | etc on OpenDoc

Value: Access is denied / Access denied
Comment: Access rights problems on OpenDoc

Value: The system is out of memory. / Out of memory
Comment: Generic error that can be thrown if engine detects the system is out of memory upon a request

Value: Not initialized / Not initialized
Comment: Not used right now but can be thrown if a system is not initialized when a request arrives for example

Value: Invalid parameters / Invalid parameters
Comment: Thrown when QV API gets invalid input parameters

Value: Some parameters are empty. / Empty parameters
Comment: Happens when engine expects parameters to certain requests but no parameters were given

Value: Internal error / Internal error
Comment: Something went wrong internally inside the engine

Value: Corrupted data / Corrupt data
Comment: For example, Problem mapping up a table in the hypercube

Value: Memory inconsistency / Memory inconsistency
Comment: Not used right now but can be used if there is a problem allocating memory inside the engine

Value: Action was aborted unexpectedly. / Invisible owner abort
Comment: Occurs when a fail check in memory allocation is triggered

Value: Validation cannot be performed at the moment. Please try again later. / Prohibit validate
Comment: Validation not possible right now

Value: Operation aborted / Request aborted
Comment: Operation was aborted internally in hypercube

Value: Connection lost. Make sure that Qlik Sense is running properly. If your session has timed out due to inactivity, refresh to continue working. / Unknown error
Comment: Message displayed in a dialog when the session has been killed/cannot be initialized due to unknown reasons.

Value: This action is not supported in the current version of Qlik Sense. / Unsupported in product version
Comment: Happens if a method is called which is not supported in the product version.

Value: An error occurred on a REST endpoint call. / Unknown error
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when there is a general problem with the REST connection such as HTTP timeout

Value: The request exceeds the memory limit. / Memory limit reached
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when the request was aborted because of the reached memory limit

Value: The request is invalid. / Bad Request
Comment: HTTP standardized error code; The request cannot be fulfilled due to bad syntax.

Value: Access is denied: the authentication has failed or has not been provided. / Unauthorized
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: Payment is required. / Payment Required
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: Access is denied. / Forbidden
Comment: HTTP standardized error code; Forbidden;

Value: The requested resource cannot be found. / Not Found
Comment: HTTP standardized error code; Not found

Value: This method is not supported. / Method Not Allowed
Comment: HTTP standardized error code;Method not allowed

Value: Not acceptable / Not Acceptable
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: Proxy authentication required / Proxy Authentication Required
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The request has timed out. / Request Timeout
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The request could not be completed due to a conflict. / Conflict
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The requested resource is no longer available. / Gone
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The content length of the request is required. / Length Required
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The precondition has failed. / Precondition Failed
Comment: HTTP standardized error code; The server does not meet one of the preconditions that the requester put on the request.

Value: The request entity is too large. / Request Entity Too Large
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The request URL is too long. / Request-URI Too Long
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The request entity's media type is not supported. / Unsupported Media Type
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The requested range is not satisfiable. / Requested Range Not Satisfiable
Comment: HTTP standardized error code; The client has asked for a portion of the file, but the server cannot supply that portion

Value: Expectation failed / Expectation Failed
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: Internal server error / Internal Server Error
Comment: HTTP standardized error code; generic error message, no specific message is suitable.

Value: The request method is not recognized or cannot be fulfilled. / Not Implemented
Comment: HTTP standardized error code; Not implemented

Value: Bad gateway / Bad Gateway
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The service is unavailable. / Service Unavailable
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: Gateway timeout / Gateway Timeout
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: The HTTP protocol version is not supported. / HTTP Version Not Supported
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: Bandwidth limit exceeded / Bandwidth Limit Exceeded
Comment: HTTP standardized error code

Value: Host could not be resolved. / Host could not be resolved
Comment: Error occurs when sending CreateConnection to an invalid url

Value: An app with this name already exists. Please choose another name. / App already exists
Comment: Happens when an application already exist when CreateApp is called

Value: An app name must not include  \\/:<>|\"?* / Invalid app name
Comment: Happens on Import App or DoSave, invalid characters in name \\/:<>|\"?*

Value: App is already open. / App already open
Comment: Happens ImportApp, OpenDoc, CreateDoc when the application is already open

Value: The app you specified could not be found. / App not found
Comment: Happens on LoadApp, the specified app could not be found

Value: The app could not be imported or created. / App import failed
Comment: Happens on ImportApp, fail to create or import an app

Value: The app could not be saved. Check if it is read only. / App save failed
Comment: Happens on DoSave, due to read only flag set or some other problem with file system/database

Value: The app was not created. / App creation failed
Comment: Happens on CreateApp, CreateDoc - correct serializer not found or some other problem saving the app after creation

Value: Failed to get app because there is no app loaded. / App invalid
Comment: Happens on GetActiveDoc when there is no active app

Value: Could not connect to the opened app. / Failed to connect to app
Comment: Happens when an user could not connect to an opened app

Value: You are trying to open an app in multiple tabs, but you cannot open an app both with and without data. / App already open in different mode
Comment: Happens when trying to open an already open app without data when the app is already open with data and vice versa

Value: The migration service could not be started. / App migration service could not be contacted
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when the migration service could not be started

Value: The app migration could not be started. / Could not start the app migration
Comment: Shown when an app migration could not be started

Value: App migration failed. Check the logs for more details. / Migration service could not migrate app
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when an app migration failed

Value: App reload failed. Synchronization of the app is in progress. / Unknown error
Comment: Happens when reloading of an app on the RIM node is triggered but the script is not yet synced

Value: App export failed. / App export failed
Comment: Shown when attempting to export and reduce an app. Likely cause: not possible to reduce the app's current state.

Value: Connection with the given name already exists. / Connection already exists
Comment: Happens when CreateConnection or ModifyConnection is called and given connection name is not unique

Value: Connection not found. / Connection not found
Comment: Happens when GetConnection, GetConnectionInfo, ModifyConnection is called and given connection name could not be found

Value: Failed to load connection. / Failed to load connection
Comment: Happens upon load of an application in QvNext and we could not load all referenced connections in the app

Value: Failed to import connection. / Failed to import connection
Comment: Happens upon ImportApp and all referenced connection belonging to the app could not be imported or created as new

Value: Invalid connection name. Please enter a new connection name of 1-256 characters, without using \ / : * ? " < > | / Connection name is invalid. Should be 1-256 characters and not contain <>:"/|?*
Comment: Happens when trying to create a connection with an invalid name

Value: Connector does not support file streaming. / Connector does not support file streaming
Comment: Shown when connector does not support file streaming.

Value: Data file size exceeded file streaming buffer size. Adjust the StreamingBufferSizeMB setting. / Data file size exceeded file streaming buffer size
Comment: Error message that appears if you attempt to stream a file larger than the StreamingBufferSize. Do not translate StreamingBufferSizeMB

Value: File access is denied. / File access denied
Comment: Happens upon OpenDoc, problem to load an app due to no access to the app file for various reasons, for instance no license or server is out of document sessionssessioner

Value: File name is invalid. / Invalid file name
Comment: Invalid file name upon DoSave app

Value: The file you are attempting to load is corrupt. Check the file for errors and try again. / File corrupted
Comment: Error message that occurs when a user tries to either load a corrupted app or corrupted excel file.

Value: A file belonging to the loaded or imported app could not be found. / File not found
Comment: Happens upon load or import of an app and the belonging file could not be found

Value: Unsupported file format / Unsupported file format version
Comment: Happens upon load or import of an app and the file format of the given app is no longer supported

Value: The file was opened in an unsupported mode. Apps with the qvw suffix cannot be opened without their data. / File opened in unsupported mode
Comment: Shown in Qlik Sense Desktop when a qvw app was opened without data which is unsupported.

Value: No table found in the HTML file. / Table not found
Comment: Shown when importing an HTML-file without a table

Value: You cannot access the requested resource. / User access denied
Comment: No access to a resource for the given user

Value: The system failed to log you in. / User impersonation failed
Comment: OpenDoc, if Username is all in hexagonal digits, validation is made and this impersonation can fail

Value: Operation aborted
Application has been deleted from memory on the engine.
Server has no more session and usage Client Access Licences. / Server out of session and usage cals
Comment: License check on OpenDoc on classic server, if the server is out of slots and the engine build number is less than 3068.

Value: Server has no more session Client Access Licences. / File not found
Comment: License check on OpenDoc  on classic server, if server is out session cals

Value: Server has no more usage Client Access Licences. / File not found
Comment: License check on OpenDoc on classic server, if server is out usage cals

Value: Server has no more Client Access Licences. / Server out of cals
Comment: Not used right now

Value: Server has no more named Client Access Licences. / Server out of named cals
Comment: License check on OpenDoc on classic server, if server is out named cals

Value: Server off duty / Server off duty
Comment: Happens when GetStreamList, GetDocList, GetAdminDocList  is called and engine is off duty

Value: Server busy / Server busy
Comment: Happens when user tries to connect to an app and server cannot handle more sessions at this point

Value: The license has expired. Please update to a current version to receive a new license. / License has expired
Comment: A Global check upon every request to engine, if the license has expired this is thrown

Value: AJAX is disabled. / Ajax disabled
Comment: Not used right now. Connected to old AJAX in classic server

Value: No usage token available for the user of this session. / No user license available for the user of this session
Comment: License check on OpenDoc on classic server, if Server can't allocate token for session user.

Value: Only AJAX clients supported with this license.
Comment: License check on OpenDoc on classic server, C++ clients denied access.

Value: Invalid hypercube object. / Invalid hypercube object
Comment: Problems with validation inside of the hypercube

Value: The hypercube results are too large. / Result too large
Comment: Problems with validation inside of the hypercube and the resulting pages are too large, i.e. over 10000 results

Value: Invalid hypercube object state. / Invalid hypercube object state
Comment: Problems with validation inside of the hypercube, no validation data exist for the specified object

Value: Not currently possible to perform the requested operation. / Function not allowed on this object in app modal mode
Comment: Thrown from hypercube when an operation is not allowed on an object because we are in modal mode for the application

Value: All expressions are disabled / All expressions disabled
Comment: Calculation error

Value: Dimension or measure not in library / Dimension or measure not in library
Comment: Calculation error

Value: Out of calculation memory / Out of object memory
Comment: Calculation error

Value: Calculation set is too large / Too many cells
Comment: Calculation error

Value: Calculation timed out / Calculation timed out
Comment: Calculation error

Value: The calculation condition is not fulfilled / Calculation condition unfulfilled
Comment: Displayed on visualization that has not fulfilled its calculation condition

Value: Mixed DBMS and in-memory aggregation is not supported / Mixed DBMS and in-memory aggregation is not supported
Comment: Calculation error; DBMS stands for database management system

Value: Direct query attempted against missing or non-direct table / Direct query attempted against missing or non-direct table
Comment: Calculation error

Value: Invalid sort order in properties / Invalid properties sort order
Comment: Calculation error, wrong sort order

Value: The calculation page is too large. Reduce the number of cells and try again. / Calculation pages too large
Comment: Calculation error, result too large

Value: Semantic fields are not allowed in calculation / Semantic fields not allowed in calculation
Comment: Calculation error, semantic fields were used

Value: The calculation of the object could not be performed successfully. Try refreshing the app. / The object is not in a valid data state
Comment: The object should have been validated, but it is invalid.

Value: The dimension is already in use. / The pivot dimensions already exist

An object is referring to a Direct Discovery field that does not exist. Please update the definition of the object or add the missing field in the Direct Discovery table. / A direct table field is missing
Comment: Do not translate "Direct Discovery"

Value: A calculation condition is not met. The dimension has been excluded from calculation. / A calculation condition stopped the calculation
Invalid identifier for the linked object / Invalid extends id for properties
Comment: Error on GetLayout the objects properties extends an invalid id

Value: Linked object not found on layout / Linked object not found on layout
Comment: Error on GetLayout and a linked object to the object is not found among the objects in the app

Value: Invalid linked object / Invalid linked object
Comment: Error on GetLayout and a linked object to the object is invalid

Value: The object could not be saved. / Write Failed
Comment: Something went wrong while persisting an object

Value: The object could not be read. / Read Failed
Comment: Something went wrong while reading a persisted object

Value: The object could not be deleted. / Delete Failed
Comment: Something went wrong while deleting persisted object

Value: The object could not be found. / Resource not found
Comment: Failed to find a specific ID related to persistance of objects

Value: You are using Qlik Sense Desktop instead of Qlik Sense, or you are using the wrong version of Qlik Sense. / Unsupported version
Comment: Sent out when client tries to do an unsupported action related to persistance. The user is performing an action on Qlik Sense Desktop that requires the full product. Or the user is doing something that is not supported in the current version .

Value: The app migration failed because the app is write-protected. / Migration failed since the file was write protected
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when the app needs upgrade and the file on disk is write-protected.

Value: The app migration was cancelled. Open the app again to migrate it. / Migration was aborted
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when the app migration was cancelled

Value: The app migration could not back up the app. The app migration is cancelled. / Backup of original file failed when migrating
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when the app migration failed to backup. The migration is cancelled.

Value: Insufficient disk space for operation / The disk is out of space
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when disk space has run out.

Value: You are trying to use a method that is not supported in session apps / Unknown error
Comment: Showed in Qlik Sense when a method that is not supported, is called on a session app

Value: Invalid parameter sent from the repository in the binary sync protocol / Invalid parameters to SetChunk
Comment: Do not translate. Related to Set Chunk. This error code is only used internally

Value: Invalid parameter sent from the repository in the binary sync protocol / Invalid parameters to GetChunk
Comment: Do not translate. Related to Get Chunk. This error code is only used internally

Value: You do not have access to the data source. / Data source access denied
Comment: Access rights problems on create new ODBC/OLEDB connection

Value: Reload in progress. / Reload in progress
Comment: A reload request from another connection in the same session is currently being processed.

Value: The following table could not be found: '{0}'. Correct the reference to the table and reload the script. / Table '{0}' not found
Comment: An error message for when a table named in a script cannot be found.

Value: The following statement could not be identified: '{0}'. Correct the syntax of this statement and reload the script. / Unknown statement: {0}
Comment: An error message for when the engine cannot figure out what statement type was intended due to a syntax error.

Value: There is a syntax problem with the following script element: '{0}'.  Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: {0}
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine expected nothing, but found the following script element: '{0}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}'  expected nothing
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. The following script element was expected: '{1}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected: '{1}'
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. One of the following script elements was expected: '{1}' or  '{2}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected one of: '{1}' , '{2}'
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. One of the following script elements was expected: '{1}', '{2}', or '{3}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected one of: '{1}' , '{2}' , '{3}'
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. One of the following script elements was expected: '{1}', '{2}', '{3}', or '{4}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected one of: '{1}' , '{2}' , '{3}' , '{4}'
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. One of the following script elements was expected: '{1}', '{2}', '{3}', '{4}', or '{5}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected one of: '{1}' , '{2}' , '{3}' , '{4}' , '{5}'
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. One of the following script elements was expected: '{1}', '{2}', '{3}', '{4}', '{5}', or '{6}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected one of: '{1}' , '{2}' , '{3}' , '{4}' , '{5}' , '{6}'
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. One of the following script elements was expected: '{1}', '{2}', '{3}', '{4}', '{5}', '{6}', or '{7}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected one of: '{1}' , '{2}',  '{3}' , '{4}' , '{5}' , '{6}' , '{7}'
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The engine found the following script element: '{0}'. Another script element was expected, such as: '{1}', '{2}', '{3}', '{4}', '{5}', '{6}', or '{7}'. Correct the syntax and reload the script. / Unexpected token: '{0}' expected one of: '{1}' , '{2}' , '{3}' , '{4}' , '{5}' , '{6}' , '{7}' ...
Comment: An error message for when the engine finds a script element

Value: The following field could not be found: '{0}'. Correct the reference to the field and reload the script. / Field '{0}' not found
Comment: An error message for when a field named in a script cannot be found.

Value: The following mapping table could not be found: '{0}'. Correct the reference to the mapping table and reload the script. / Mapping table '{0}' not found
Comment: An error message for when a mapping table that was named in the script cannot be found.

Value: The following connection could not be found: '{0}'. Correct the reference to the connection and reload the script. / Connection '{0}' not found
Comment: An error message for when a connection that was named in the script cannot.  From script like: LIB CONNECT TO [lib://database]

Value: This name already exists: '{0}'. Select a different name for the rename operation and reload the script. / The name '{0}' already exists.
Comment: An error message for when the name selected for a rename operation is already in use.

Value: The file is in an incorrect format or may be damaged. Save the file in DIF format and reload the script. / Unsupported or bad format in DIF file
Comment: An error message for when a DIF file is specified but the file it is pointing to is not in the DIF format or is too damaged to be recognized. Do not translate [DIF].

Value: The file is in an incorrect format or may be damaged. Save the file in BIFF format and reload the script. / Unsupported or bad format in BIFF file
Comment: An error message for when a BIFF file is specified but the file it is pointing to is not in the BIFF format or is too damaged to be recognized. Do not translate [BIFF].

Value: Cannot read an Excel file protected by passwords. Remove the password and reload the script. / Cannot read file because it is encrypted
Comment: An error message for when the excel file selected to load data from is password protected and inaccessible to Sense. Do not translate [Excel].

Value: Cannot open the following file: '{0}'. Check to confirm that the file is available and reload the script. / Cannot open file: '{0}'
Comment: An error message for when a file is specified in a script, but cannot be opened due to the file not existing, the system not having the rights to open it, the file being already opened and locked by another program, or another cause of the file being made inaccessible.

Value: The following autogenerate number is incorrect: '{0}'. Autogenerate numbers cannot be negative numbers or greater than 2147483647. Correct the autogenerate number and reload the script. / Invalid Autogenerate count: {0}
Comment: An error message for when the autogenerate number, that is the number of records the autogenerate statement is generating, of a LOAD statement is invalid. Typically a negative number or too large like more than 2^31. Do not translate [autogenerate]

Value: These LOAD statement prefixes cannot be combined. Remove the conflicting prefixes and reload. / Illegal combination of prefixes
Comment: An error message for when a LOAD statement includes conflicting prefixes, such as JOIN and NONCONCATENATE. Do not translate [LOAD]

Value: The control statement does not match its corresponding start statement. Confirm that the start and end of the control statement are formatted correctly and reload. / The control statement is not correctly matched with its corresponding start statement.
Comment: An error message for when a Control statement that has a start and end part, such as IF ... and the corresponding end if, does not have matching start and end parts.

Value: The following connection could not be found: {0}. Correct the reference to the connection or confirm you have access rights to this connection, and reload. / Connection not found: {0}
Comment: An error message for when the connection specified cannot be found.

Value: The following connection is invalid: {0}.  Correct the reference to the connection and reload. / Connection {0} is invalid
Comment: An error message for when the connection specified exists but something is wrong with its definition.

Value: The following path is outside the folder defined by the connection: '{0}'. Enter the complete path and reload the script. / The path '{0}' is outside the folder defined by the connection
Comment: An error message for when a path is probably using .. to escape the file system root, which is not allowed.

Value: There is no qualified path for the following file: {0}. Save your QlikView document before using qualify statements. / No qualified path for file: {0}
Comment: An error message for when a path is missing a qualified path. This specific message will only come when using relative paths and the app/document is not saved

Value: This statement only works with lib:// paths in standard mode. Change your statement to use a lib:// path and reload the script. / This statement only works with lib:// paths in this script mode
Comment: An error message for when LOAD is used with a path other than a Lib path in standard mode. Do not translate [lib://]

Value: Inconsistent use of semantic fields. Correct the use of the semantic prefix and reload the script. / Inconsistent use of semantic fields
Comment: An error message for when semantic fields are used inconsistently. Do Not Translate [semantic].

Value: There is no open data connection. There may be a missing or failed CONNECT statement. Check your CONNECT statement, confirm the connection is accessible, and reload the script. / There is no open data connection.
Comment: An error message for when where is no open data connection, likely as the result of a SELECT statement missing a successful CONNECT statement before it, but also potentially because the database is unavailable or the database account is invalid. Do not translate [CONNECT].

Value: The GROUP BY clause requires aggregation expressions. Add aggregation expressions to the clause and reload the script. / Aggregation expressions required by GROUP BY clause.
Comment: An error message for when a GROUP BY clause is missing aggregation expressions such as SUM or COUNT. Do not translate: [GROUP BY].

Value: CONNECT statements other than LIB CONNECT are not available in this script mode. Change the CONNECT statement to LIB CONNECT and reload the script. / CONNECTs other than LIB CONNECT are not available in this script mode.
Comment: An error message for when a CONNECT statement is used in the incorrect script mode. Do not translate: CONNECT, LIB CONNECT. Do not translate [CONNECT, LIB CONNECT]

Value: ODBC connection failed. Check to see if the database is available and that it is identified correctly in the script. / ODBC connection failed
Comment: An error message for when a ODBC connection fails. Do not translate [ODBC]

Value: OLEDB connection failed. Check to see if the database is available and that it is identified correctly in the script. / OLEDB connection failed
Comment: An error message for when a OLEDB connection fails. Do not translate [OLEDB]

Value: Custom connection failed. Check to see if the database is available and that it is identified correctly in the script. / Custom connection failed
Comment: An error message for when a custom connection fails.

Value: ODBC read failed. Check to see if the database is available and that it is identified correctly in the script. / ODBC read failed
Comment: An error message for when a ODBC read fails. Do not translate [ODBC]

Value: OLEDB read failed. Check to see if the database is available and that it is identified correctly in the script. / OLEDB read failed
Comment: An error message for when a OLEDB read fails. Do not translate [OLEDB]

Value: Custom read failed. Check to see if the database is available and that it is identified correctly in the script. / Custom read failed
Comment: An error message for when a Custom read fails.

Value: Binary load is not allowed with the following document: {0}. / Binary Load is not allowed on: {0}
Comment: An error message for when Binary LOAD is attempted on a document that has been marked as protected from Binary LOAD. It could be sensitive data and the admin disabled it. Do not translate [binary LOAD]

Value: The following connector failed to start: {0}. The connector cannot be found or the system is missing DLLs for the connector. Contact your system administrator. / Failed to start connector: {0}
Comment: An error message for when a connector fails to start. This could be from the system missing DLL for the connector or the system being unable to find the connector. Do not translate [DLL]

Value: The connector is not responding. Contact your system administrator. / Connector is not responding
Comment: An error message for when a connector is not responding.

Value: The connector has returned the following error: {0}. / Connector reply error: {0}
Comment: An error message for when the connector failed to perform a task and returned an error

Value: Connector connect error: {0}. / Connector connect error: {0}
Comment: The CONNECT statment

Value: Custom connector {0} was not found. / Connector {0} not found
Comment: Custom connector type is probably not supported. Only supported extensions are .exe and .dll.

Value: Duplicate keys found when loading Input Field {0}. / Duplicate keys when loading Input Field {0}
There is no previously loaded table to perform a Concatenate LOAD with. / No previous table for concatenate load.
There is a new version of Qlik Sense Desktop available. Please update to the new version. / New Qlik Sense Desktop version available
Comment: Showed when we have a new version of the product available

Value: Your version of Qlik Sense Desktop has expired. / This engine has expired
Comment: Showed when the product  is outdated

Value: Section access information was detected. This is not supported in Qlik Sense Desktop. To be able to load data into Qlik Sense Desktop, make sure to remove any section access information using a version that supports this. / Section access detected when opening an app
Comment: Showed when Qlik Sense Desktop detects section access in the app upon load

Value: Because the app is open, it cannot be deleted. Please close the app and try again. / Unknown error
Comment: Showed when an already opened app is about to be deleted in Qlik Sense Desktop

Value: User is not authenticated. Please log in to Qlik Sense Desktop. / User authentication failure
Comment: Showed when an Engine API is called before the user has authenticated in Sense Desktop

Value: You have reached the size limitation of the export process. Please reduce the number of values to export or change the settings. / Out of memory
Comment: Shown when an export fails due to reaching the limits set in the settings.ini configuration file.

Value: There is no data to export. Please make sure the data in your visualization is correct. / No data

Value: File with the given offset was not found. / Unknown error
Comment: Error message
